definition: to (a place)/until (a time)/up to/to go/to arrive/(verb complement denoting completion or result of an action)

sentences.english: The goods submitted do not corresppond with the sample sent.
sentences.chinese: 到貨與惠送樣品並不相同。

sentences.english: At present this model of product already receipted Chongqing , has a look together .
sentences.chinese: 目前這款產品已經到貨重慶，一起來看看。

sentences.english: In charge of checking and accepting for all utility equipments or machines to be maintained.
sentences.chinese: 負責動力設備零備件及材料計劃，到貨驗收及保管。

sentences.english: The shop decided to clear off the winter clothes when the new summer fashions arrived.
sentences.chinese: 當新的夏季時裝到貨以後，該店決定降價出售冬裝。

sentences.english: The consignees shall keep the rights for final inspection and claims after the goods are received.
sentences.chinese: 收貨人保留到貨後最終檢驗和索賠的權利。

sentences.english: Several long-awaited videos will finally arrive in the shops this month.
sentences.chinese: 幾部讓人翹首企盼的錄像片終於將在這個月到貨。

sentences.english: The inspection should be completed within a month after the arrival of the goods。
sentences.chinese: 商品檢驗工作在到貨後一個月內完成。

sentences.english: The pumpkin seed oil and tea tree shampoo you ordered have arrived.
sentences.chinese: 您訂購的南瓜子油和茶樹洗髮精已經到貨了。

sentences.english: Four to five weeks, probably, though I can not guarantee any particular dare .
sentences.chinese: 大概四五星期到貨，不過我不能保證哪一天到。

sentences.english: In charge of management on spare parts for all utility equipment or machines.
sentences.chinese: 負責動力設備零備件及材料計劃，到貨驗收及保管。

sentences.english: Please send me the Booking Notice with the ETD & ETA for the following shipment ASAP.
sentences.chinese: 請儘快通知我方以下船運的預計發貨時間及到貨時間。

sentences.english: The typical assays shall be close to the actual quality.
sentences.chinese: 該典型分析值應與實際到貨品質保持相近。

sentences.english: The shortage in net weight of delivered cargo was due to insufficiency of originally dispatched weight.
sentences.chinese: 到貨淨重短少，系原發貨重量不足所致。

sentences.english: The October shipment of canned fruits arrived in a worthless state.
sentences.chinese: 10月份裝運的那批水果罐頭到貨時情況糟透了。

sentences.english: Under ordinary circumstances, seven workdays arrive.
sentences.chinese: 普通狀況下七個任務日到貨。

definition: to take a customer's order/(of a taxi driver) to accept a booking/(of a delivery rider) to accept a delivery job
to take money or valuables out of storage/to recover/to ship goods/to extract (chemicals from solution)
to place an order/to order/an order (of goods)
to order goods/to place an order
